Zimbabwe's President Mnangagwa escapes explosion at rally Mr Mnangagwa described Mrs Mugabe as someone who had frequently insulted him in the past. "On what basis would I trust someone who was used by a cabal to say things that had no basis," he said. Despite the apparent attempt on his life, Mr Mnangagwa said Zimbabwe was stable and that foreign investors should not worry. There would be no countrywide security clampdown and elections scheduled for next month would go ahead in a free and fair manner, he said.